    <title>IPv4 address ranges</title>
    
    <para>
        The assignment of IP addresses is not arbitrary: Several discrete <emphasis>blocks</emphasis> of addresses are defined,
        which govern their applicability and behaviour. The block sizes denote a range of addresses. For example, the block
        starting at <literal>0.0.0.0</literal> with size <literal>8</literal> specifies an address range of <literal>0.0.0.0</literal> - 
        <literal>0.0.0.255</literal>.
    </para>
    
