    <para>
        <emphasis>Private networks</emphasis> are used within a company or home network, and these addresses are not allowed to communicate
        directly on the public internet without <abbrev>NAT</abbrev> (Network Address Translation).
    </para>
    
    <para>
        Data sent to a <emphasis>Multicast</emphasis> addresses is sent to one or more interested recipients simultaneously (known as 
        multicast <emphasis>groups</emphasis>), without the sender having to know their individual addresses, and without
        incurring a performance or bandwidth overhead.
    </para>
    
    <para>
        Data sent to a <emphasis>Broadcast</emphasis> address is sent to all nodes on the local network.
    </para>
    
    
